1
00:01:24,710 --> 00:01:25,836
Catherine, don't!

2
00:01:34,344 --> 00:01:35,386
It's still warm.

3
00:01:35,387 --> 00:01:37,514
And since the teacup accidentally broke...

4
00:01:38,140 --> 00:01:40,434
the culprit needs to make another kill,

5
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:42,603
to ensure that I got the message.

6
00:01:42,686 --> 00:01:45,272
I have your scandal.

7
00:01:46,273 --> 00:01:48,358
And if you don’t drink this,

8
00:01:49,651 --> 00:01:51,904
I’ll make sure it gets out.

9
00:01:52,654 --> 00:01:54,114
Drink this,

10
00:01:55,407 --> 00:02:00,329
because if you don't,
I'll leak your videos.

11
00:02:37,783 --> 00:02:38,783
Loki!

12
00:02:39,201 --> 00:02:40,201
Loki!

13
00:02:42,162 --> 00:02:43,413
Help!

14
00:02:43,705 --> 00:02:45,207
Help!

15
00:02:46,917 --> 00:02:49,336
Loki, wake up! Please, wake up!

16
00:02:54,424 --> 00:02:56,677
♪ Shadows ♪

17
00:02:56,775 --> 00:02:59,486
♪ in the dark are crawling. ♪

18
00:03:00,389 --> 00:03:04,433
♪ Keeping watch and barring your way. ♪

19
00:03:04,434 --> 00:03:07,980
♪ As if the line could not be crossed. ♪

20
00:03:08,939 --> 00:03:12,525
♪ To every scream and every tremor. ♪

21
00:03:12,526 --> 00:03:15,695
♪ These walls remain the only witness. ♪

22
00:03:15,696 --> 00:03:18,656
♪ Every noise is etched in here. ♪

23
00:03:18,657 --> 00:03:23,161
♪ Like fire and ammunition
for your memory. ♪

24
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:26,427
♪ Heed the warnings. ♪

25
00:03:27,671 --> 00:03:30,049
♪ The threats poised to strike. ♪

26
00:03:31,133 --> 00:03:34,803
♪ For this world ♪

27
00:03:35,471 --> 00:03:38,097
♪ is not what you imagined. ♪

28
00:03:38,098 --> 00:03:40,559
♪ Heed the warnings. ♪

29
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:43,687
♪ Open up your eyes. ♪

30
00:03:44,980 --> 00:03:48,525
♪ For this world ♪

31
00:03:49,234 --> 00:03:51,778
♪ is not what you imagined. ♪

32
00:03:51,779 --> 00:03:56,617
♪ Heed the warnings. ♪

33
00:06:10,834 --> 00:06:13,378
No. No! No!

34
00:06:14,922 --> 00:06:17,090
Lorelei! No!

35
00:06:19,551 --> 00:06:20,551
No.

36
00:06:20,969 --> 00:06:22,638
Lorelei, wake up.

37
00:06:22,804 --> 00:06:24,096
No!

38
00:06:24,097 --> 00:06:25,224
No!

39
00:06:26,016 --> 00:06:27,016
Lorelei!

40
00:06:27,643 --> 00:06:29,061
No!

41
00:06:38,111 --> 00:06:39,196
Lorelei!

42
00:06:40,239 --> 00:06:41,614
Don't die on me!

43
00:06:41,615 --> 00:06:42,574
Wake up!

44
00:06:42,574 --> 00:06:43,574
Lorelei.

45
00:06:46,161 --> 00:06:47,496
No!

46
00:07:21,393 --> 00:07:22,393
Is that you?

47
00:07:24,354 --> 00:07:25,354
Rhea,

48
00:07:26,388 --> 00:07:27,764
what are you doing here?

49
00:07:30,819 --> 00:07:31,819
How…

50
00:07:31,945 --> 00:07:33,780
You’re the detective here, aren’t you?

51
00:07:34,156 --> 00:07:35,657
You tell me.

52
00:07:37,284 --> 00:07:38,994
The real culprit

53
00:07:39,661 --> 00:07:40,661
is…

54
00:07:41,004 --> 00:07:42,213
Daniel Geronimo.

55
00:07:44,916 --> 00:07:48,712
I know you can solve this puzzle, Loki.

56
00:07:51,590 --> 00:07:55,051
So we’re going to play a drinking game.

57
00:07:55,469 --> 00:07:58,888
One contains belladonna,

58
00:07:58,889 --> 00:08:02,726
and the other is just regular tea.

59
00:08:11,860 --> 00:08:12,860
Loki!

60
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:14,321
Loki!

61
00:08:16,114 --> 00:08:17,115
Loki…

62
00:08:23,121 --> 00:08:24,289
This is not real.

63
00:08:25,373 --> 00:08:27,125
You really never change.

64
00:08:28,418 --> 00:08:30,962
You always try to logic your way
through everything.

65
00:08:31,755 --> 00:08:33,757
But look what happened to you.

66
00:08:33,882 --> 00:08:35,008
Oh, please!

67
00:08:35,926 --> 00:08:37,594
You know me better than I am.

68
00:08:38,386 --> 00:08:40,305
You know me better than anyone else.

69
00:08:41,556 --> 00:08:43,141
Is Lori the new me now?

70
00:08:46,102 --> 00:08:48,271
No matter how many people I meet...

71
00:08:50,857 --> 00:08:52,400
no one could replace you.

72
00:08:54,361 --> 00:08:56,362
Do you know she’s been watching over you

73
00:08:56,363 --> 00:08:58,406
ever since she brought you
here at the hospital?

74
00:08:59,699 --> 00:09:00,866
She was almost crying

75
00:09:00,867 --> 00:09:03,994
while the doctors pumped
the belladonna out of your system.

76
00:09:03,995 --> 00:09:05,664
She truly cares for you.

77
00:09:06,790 --> 00:09:09,125
I noticed you two seem a lot alike.

78
00:09:11,795 --> 00:09:12,921
In what way?

79
00:09:14,005 --> 00:09:15,757
You’re in the same situation.

80
00:09:16,049 --> 00:09:18,385
You have the same attitude.

81
00:09:19,219 --> 00:09:22,639
Just like you,
she doesn’t trust people easily.

82
00:09:23,348 --> 00:09:24,849
But now it feels like…

83
00:09:25,934 --> 00:09:28,103
you’re finally comfortable
with each other.

84
00:09:35,986 --> 00:09:38,321
No. I don’t think so.

85
00:09:39,864 --> 00:09:42,158
I’m not even sure
if she wants to be friends with me.

86
00:09:42,409 --> 00:09:43,410
Really?

87
00:09:43,952 --> 00:09:47,414
You practically turned the Q.E.D. Club
into your home on campus.

88
00:09:48,123 --> 00:09:50,458
She wouldn’t be there
if she had so many other friends.

89
00:09:51,376 --> 00:09:53,044
I forced her to join the club.

90
00:09:54,087 --> 00:09:56,506
I'm not sure if she enjoys being a member.

91
00:09:56,798 --> 00:09:59,134
She doesn’t look like she’s being forced.

92
00:09:59,718 --> 00:10:03,430
She could always skip club activities
or the cases.

93
00:10:03,888 --> 00:10:05,932
But, look, she's always present.

94
00:10:06,975 --> 00:10:07,975
Fair point.

95
00:10:08,935 --> 00:10:10,520
What does she mean to you?

96
00:10:11,104 --> 00:10:14,733
Is she just a club member,
or another puzzle you need to solve?

97
00:10:15,275 --> 00:10:17,277
Why are we even talking about her?

98
00:10:19,738 --> 00:10:21,238
You really don’t get it, do you?

99
00:10:21,239 --> 00:10:22,239
Get what?

100
00:10:23,325 --> 00:10:24,492
Just tell me already.

101
00:10:24,993 --> 00:10:27,871
You know it already.
You’re just denying it.

102
00:10:28,455 --> 00:10:31,333
Does it really have to come from me?

103
00:10:31,916 --> 00:10:34,461
How many months has it been, Loki?

104
00:10:35,003 --> 00:10:37,088
Six? Seven?

105
00:10:38,089 --> 00:10:41,009
Even now,
you still haven’t moved on from M.

106
00:10:41,760 --> 00:10:46,306
You keep chasing him to the point
that it has become your obsession.

107
00:10:47,599 --> 00:10:49,267
I’m doing this for you, Rhea.

108
00:10:50,060 --> 00:10:51,519
To give you justice.

109
00:10:52,354 --> 00:10:53,980
Is it really for me?

110
00:10:54,731 --> 00:10:57,901
Okay, fine. I understand you.

111
00:10:58,026 --> 00:10:59,861
I know where you’re coming from.

112
00:11:00,862 --> 00:11:03,448
But where has chasing him gotten you?

113
00:11:04,407 --> 00:11:06,159
You’re putting yourself in danger.

114
00:11:07,285 --> 00:11:08,912
I just want to make it up to you.

115
00:11:11,581 --> 00:11:12,707
You’re dead

116
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:14,750
because…

117
00:11:18,546 --> 00:11:20,006
because you’re friends with me.

118
00:11:20,382 --> 00:11:23,802
So why did you recruit Lori
in the first place?

119
00:11:26,638 --> 00:11:31,476
The Q.E.D. Club will be dissolved
if there are no other members left.

120
00:11:32,936 --> 00:11:35,563
We both know that’s not true.

121
00:11:36,439 --> 00:11:37,816
Just admit it already.

122
00:11:38,525 --> 00:11:40,819
You need someone to talk to too, Loki.

123
00:11:41,361 --> 00:11:42,612
You’re lonely.

124
00:11:43,113 --> 00:11:46,408
And it’s okay for you
to make a new friend.

125
00:11:46,866 --> 00:11:51,413
You can’t keep depending on me
when I’m no longer in this world.

126
00:11:53,039 --> 00:11:56,584
But I hope your new friends help you

127
00:11:57,210 --> 00:12:00,087
move on with your life
and stop chasing Moriarty.

128
00:12:00,088 --> 00:12:01,464
I can’t do that.

129
00:12:02,966 --> 00:12:04,426
I can’t just let him be.

130
00:12:06,010 --> 00:12:07,469
Once I catch him,

131
00:12:07,470 --> 00:12:10,390
that’s when I can finally have
some peace.

132
00:12:11,599 --> 00:12:14,227
That’s when I can actually move on.

133
00:12:15,437 --> 00:12:17,272
You’re still so stubborn.

134
00:12:19,023 --> 00:12:20,942
That’s why you keep getting into trouble.

135
00:12:21,943 --> 00:12:24,279
And the people around you too.

136
00:12:25,321 --> 00:12:27,115
Listen to me, Loki.

137
00:12:28,742 --> 00:12:30,325
I’m telling you,

138
00:12:30,326 --> 00:12:35,582
catching Moriarty doesn’t matter
because I’m no longer in this world.

139
00:12:35,915 --> 00:12:37,292
There’s no point anymore.

140
00:12:37,917 --> 00:12:39,461
Am I going to live?

141
00:12:40,170 --> 00:12:41,421
Not anymore, right?

142
00:12:41,713 --> 00:12:46,468
You’re clinging to your guilt so much,
you don’t realize that it’s hurting you.

143
00:12:46,718 --> 00:12:51,556
Instead of wasting your time,
why not just enjoy your life?

144
00:12:52,557 --> 00:12:54,642
Life is precious, Loki.

145
00:12:59,063 --> 00:13:01,107
Maybe someday, I will.

146
00:13:02,025 --> 00:13:03,026
I don’t know.

147
00:13:04,235 --> 00:13:06,112
Looks like it’s time for me to go.

148
00:13:07,405 --> 00:13:09,365
I missed our conversations.

149
00:13:09,741 --> 00:13:10,741
Wait.

150
00:13:11,326 --> 00:13:12,410
Where are you going?

151
00:13:17,665 --> 00:13:19,459
Have you forgiven me, Rhea?

152
00:13:24,506 --> 00:13:25,507
Rhea...

153
00:13:26,633 --> 00:13:27,634
don't go.

154
00:13:28,092 --> 00:13:30,512
I’m not the one
who should forgive you, Loki.

155
00:13:31,012 --> 00:13:32,764
You’ve done nothing wrong to me.

156
00:13:34,140 --> 00:13:36,351
You’re the one who needs
to forgive yourself.

157
00:14:33,032 --> 00:14:34,032
Hey.

158
00:14:34,659 --> 00:14:36,035
Wake up, sleepy head.

159
00:14:43,835 --> 00:14:44,835
Loki?

160
00:14:46,212 --> 00:14:47,212
Loki!

161
00:14:49,799 --> 00:14:50,799
Loki.

162
00:14:51,342 --> 00:14:53,511
You’re alive! You're awake!

163
00:14:54,387 --> 00:14:55,638
I can’t believe that.

164
00:14:57,473 --> 00:14:59,142
What’s with the overreaction?

165
00:15:00,685 --> 00:15:03,688
Wait, I can’t breathe.
You can let go of me now.

166
00:15:04,564 --> 00:15:06,024
I might actually die.

167
00:15:06,065 --> 00:15:08,526
Sorry, I’m just really happy.

168
00:15:10,320 --> 00:15:11,612
But, what...

169
00:15:11,613 --> 00:15:12,780
Have a seat.

170
00:15:13,656 --> 00:15:17,367
Are you hungry? Thirsty? What do you need?

171
00:15:17,368 --> 00:15:19,495
- Nurse! Nurse...
- Okay.

172
00:15:19,704 --> 00:15:21,331
Lorelei, I’m okay.

173
00:15:22,165 --> 00:15:23,165
Okay.

174
00:15:26,210 --> 00:15:27,378
Are you feeling dizzy?

175
00:15:31,758 --> 00:15:33,134
Don’t stress yourself out.

176
00:15:36,387 --> 00:15:37,388
Slowly.

177
00:15:41,225 --> 00:15:42,225
Wait.

178
00:15:42,769 --> 00:15:44,062
How did I get here?

179
00:15:46,189 --> 00:15:49,484
Don’t tell me
you carried me here from campus?

180
00:15:50,485 --> 00:15:53,613
I might’ve carried you myself
if I hadn’t gotten help.

181
00:15:54,697 --> 00:15:56,532
Loki, wake up!

182
00:15:56,824 --> 00:15:59,452
Help. Help!

183
00:16:00,954 --> 00:16:02,246
Help!

184
00:16:03,665 --> 00:16:05,583
- Loki's unconscious.
- Loki!

185
00:16:06,209 --> 00:16:08,044
Loki! Loki!

186
00:16:10,463 --> 00:16:11,631
Help!

187
00:16:12,298 --> 00:16:13,675
Get some help here!

188
00:16:14,592 --> 00:16:15,592
Help.

189
00:16:20,974 --> 00:16:25,061
Good thing Professor Morayta
was near the clubroom

190
00:16:25,353 --> 00:16:27,605
and called for help right away,

191
00:16:27,939 --> 00:16:30,233
to bring you here at the hospital.

192
00:16:33,069 --> 00:16:35,321
Prof... Professor Morayta?

193
00:16:36,197 --> 00:16:39,367
Yes, my Math 100 professor.

194
00:16:40,076 --> 00:16:42,745
And our client in the Stein Alberts' case.

195
00:16:43,454 --> 00:16:44,454
Remember?

196
00:16:44,831 --> 00:16:46,708
Yeah. I remember now.

197
00:16:47,750 --> 00:16:51,087
Sorry, my mind is still in a haze.

198
00:16:51,337 --> 00:16:52,337
It’s okay.

199
00:16:52,630 --> 00:16:57,218
Besides, I’m really bad at remembering
the names of past clients or victims.

200
00:16:57,719 --> 00:16:58,803
I noticed that too.

201
00:16:59,721 --> 00:17:04,100
Hey, if you see Prof,
be sure to thank him, okay?

202
00:17:10,106 --> 00:17:12,233
Don’t push yourself too hard yet, okay?

203
00:17:13,568 --> 00:17:15,153
The doctor said to me,

204
00:17:15,987 --> 00:17:18,363
there are still traces of belladonna
in your system,

205
00:17:18,364 --> 00:17:20,700
so you might still feel its effects.

206
00:17:21,826 --> 00:17:24,620
So you need to get plenty of rest, okay?

207
00:17:25,413 --> 00:17:27,582
Got it. Thank you.

208
00:17:30,752 --> 00:17:34,589
By the way, what happened
to my drinking buddy?

209
00:17:35,131 --> 00:17:36,382
Is he alive?

210
00:17:37,425 --> 00:17:39,510
Can we interrogate him?

211
00:17:44,140 --> 00:17:47,351
Loki! Please stay with me, Loki.

212
00:17:48,227 --> 00:17:49,604
Hang in there, Loki!

213
00:17:51,606 --> 00:17:52,899
Stay with me, Loki.

214
00:17:53,066 --> 00:17:55,610
Don't die on me, Loki! Come on!

215
00:17:57,320 --> 00:17:58,946
Keep breathing, Loki!

216
00:17:59,322 --> 00:18:00,322
Keep fighting!

217
00:18:07,872 --> 00:18:09,040
Stay with me.

218
00:18:15,588 --> 00:18:16,964
He didn’t make it.

219
00:18:18,049 --> 00:18:20,593
The doctors suspect he was poisoned.

220
00:18:21,761 --> 00:18:23,971
They’re already performing
an autopsy on his body.

221
00:18:27,517 --> 00:18:29,268
Is it because of belladonna?

222
00:18:29,727 --> 00:18:30,895
It’s possible.

223
00:18:31,187 --> 00:18:33,648
Looks like you both ingested belladonna.

224
00:18:34,857 --> 00:18:36,776
But based on the initial findings,

225
00:18:37,276 --> 00:18:39,487
it looks like he got the one with poison.

226
00:18:41,280 --> 00:18:44,491
Later, a campus police officer
will stop by

227
00:18:44,492 --> 00:18:46,410
to give us a copy of the report.

228
00:18:47,286 --> 00:18:49,956
Whoever gave him those tea bags...

229
00:18:51,040 --> 00:18:52,166
set him up.

230
00:18:52,875 --> 00:18:56,838
He wasn't told that one of the teacups
was laced with poison.

231
00:18:59,340 --> 00:19:00,424
Lorelei...

232
00:19:02,385 --> 00:19:04,220
just a small favor, please?

233
00:19:06,097 --> 00:19:08,224
Could you leave out what happened to me

234
00:19:08,724 --> 00:19:11,686
when you write out
your blog post about the case?

235
00:19:12,186 --> 00:19:13,186
What?

236
00:19:13,688 --> 00:19:14,688
Why?

237
00:19:16,232 --> 00:19:18,234
I just don’t want to make things worse.

238
00:19:19,110 --> 00:19:21,863
This may negatively impact our club.

239
00:19:22,280 --> 00:19:23,364
No, Loki!

240
00:19:23,698 --> 00:19:26,826
People should know what happened to you.

241
00:19:27,285 --> 00:19:29,579
We need to be transparent to all

242
00:19:29,745 --> 00:19:32,914
so they know even the Q.E.D. Club

243
00:19:32,915 --> 00:19:36,419
isn’t immune to the violence
and killings happening in this school.

244
00:19:37,378 --> 00:19:40,590
Sorry, but I’ll have to decline
your request.

245
00:19:48,681 --> 00:19:51,391
Okay, Luthor. Let me handle this.

246
00:19:51,392 --> 00:19:52,268
Thank you, Em.

247
00:19:52,269 --> 00:19:54,687
I just have something important
to attend to.

248
00:19:55,062 --> 00:19:56,062
No worries.

249
00:19:56,355 --> 00:19:57,355
It's okay.

250
00:20:02,320 --> 00:20:03,362
Good day.

251
00:20:03,988 --> 00:20:05,823
This is Emeraude Emerson.

252
00:20:06,282 --> 00:20:08,409
Your Student Council President.

253
00:20:10,036 --> 00:20:13,038
I know that we're all
being deeply affected

254
00:20:13,039 --> 00:20:15,333
by the recent deaths in our campus.

255
00:20:15,625 --> 00:20:19,670
In the previous cases,
it’s always been murder.

256
00:20:20,379 --> 00:20:22,423
And the culprits are caught right away.

257
00:20:22,924 --> 00:20:24,466
But the recent deaths,

258
00:20:24,467 --> 00:20:27,762
the victims have taken their own lives.

259
00:20:29,597 --> 00:20:32,975
And who is to blame for
with these cases?

260
00:20:33,517 --> 00:20:34,518
No one.

261
00:20:35,061 --> 00:20:36,061
No one at all.

262
00:20:37,521 --> 00:20:40,690
But, perhaps, they are the products
of inadequate support

263
00:20:40,691 --> 00:20:44,278
for the mental health
of the students here in Clark U.

264
00:20:44,487 --> 00:20:47,405
And maybe they don’t even realize

265
00:20:47,406 --> 00:20:50,576
they're struggling
psychologically and emotionally.

266
00:20:50,910 --> 00:20:54,080
That’s why I ask everyone of you,

267
00:20:54,288 --> 00:20:57,583
to please be kind
and look out for one another.

268
00:20:57,917 --> 00:21:01,294
Thank you, Student Council President,
Emeraude Emerson.

269
00:21:01,295 --> 00:21:03,965
Excuse me!
Is it true the victims were murdered?

270
00:21:04,298 --> 00:21:07,676
I read in the Q.E.D. Chronicle
that they were murdered!

271
00:21:07,677 --> 00:21:10,303
I don’t believe the Q.E.D.
that every case has a killer!

272
00:21:10,304 --> 00:21:12,389
What is it with these students?
Are they killers?

273
00:21:12,390 --> 00:21:15,016
What kind of school is this,
a nest of criminals?

274
00:21:15,017 --> 00:21:16,476
Exactly!

275
00:21:16,477 --> 00:21:19,479
Those Q.E.D. people are just rage bait.

276
00:21:19,480 --> 00:21:21,314
- That’s right! That’s right!
- Right?

277
00:21:21,315 --> 00:21:22,983
- That’s true!
- They’re all just clout chasers!

278
00:21:22,984 --> 00:21:24,067
Right, isn’t it?

279
00:21:24,068 --> 00:21:25,944
Hey! You guys are too much!

280
00:21:25,945 --> 00:21:29,281
They’re the ones
helping catch the culprits!

281
00:21:29,282 --> 00:21:30,950
- Stop being such haters!
- That’s right!

282
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:32,243
That's right!

283
00:21:33,869 --> 00:21:36,454
- They’re just clout-chasing.
- Your club’s full of killers!

284
00:21:36,455 --> 00:21:38,331
Your club’s full of killers!

285
00:21:38,332 --> 00:21:41,001
- And you’re still defending them?
- They’re the ones helping.

286
00:21:41,002 --> 00:21:43,086
Everyone here is a killer.

287
00:21:43,087 --> 00:21:45,089
That's true. Everyone! What?

288
00:21:47,258 --> 00:21:48,718
They're the ones helping.

289
00:21:59,103 --> 00:22:00,396
Where are you going?

290
00:22:06,360 --> 00:22:07,653
Where are you going?

291
00:22:08,738 --> 00:22:10,071
I have to go to the restroom.

292
00:22:10,072 --> 00:22:12,408
Then, I'll call the nurse.

293
00:22:13,117 --> 00:22:15,202
Lorelei, I can do it.

294
00:22:15,995 --> 00:22:17,038
Are you sure?

295
00:22:17,121 --> 00:22:18,122
Yeah.

296
00:22:19,957 --> 00:22:20,957
Move!

297
00:22:21,208 --> 00:22:22,208
Be careful.

298
00:22:25,713 --> 00:22:26,714
Loki.

299
00:22:31,844 --> 00:22:33,387
See? I told you.

300
00:22:33,971 --> 00:22:34,972
You’re so stubborn.

301
00:22:35,639 --> 00:22:37,141
Let me help you.

302
00:22:41,312 --> 00:22:42,563
Slowly.

303
00:22:48,986 --> 00:22:50,529
- Oh, no. It's locked.
- Just open it.

304
00:22:51,113 --> 00:22:52,281
I think I locked it.

305
00:22:52,948 --> 00:22:54,742
I think, I locked it. Sorry.

306
00:22:56,827 --> 00:22:58,162
Let’s just go outside.

307
00:22:59,413 --> 00:23:00,748
Okay.

308
00:23:03,042 --> 00:23:04,042
I got it.

309
00:23:08,714 --> 00:23:09,714
Take care.

310
00:23:17,473 --> 00:23:19,016
There, there's the restroom.

311
00:23:19,642 --> 00:23:20,810
I'll take care of that.

312
00:23:29,610 --> 00:23:30,653
Take it easy.

313
00:23:31,862 --> 00:23:32,905
Take care.

314
00:23:34,615 --> 00:23:35,616
Okay.

315
00:23:41,956 --> 00:23:42,956
I can do it now.

316
00:23:43,624 --> 00:23:44,624
- You...
- You may go!

317
00:23:44,917 --> 00:23:46,127
You might fall.

318
00:23:48,546 --> 00:23:52,258
What if you fall
or you hit your head or something?

319
00:23:54,677 --> 00:23:57,805
No, why are you coming with me
into the restroom?

320
00:23:58,431 --> 00:24:00,057
I don’t know, I mean...

321
00:24:00,474 --> 00:24:02,768
maybe you might need my assistance?

322
00:24:06,063 --> 00:24:07,064
Assistance?

323
00:24:08,816 --> 00:24:09,816
Really?

324
00:24:12,528 --> 00:24:13,946
Eww! Loki!

325
00:24:14,989 --> 00:24:16,073
You know what,

326
00:24:16,449 --> 00:24:17,700
I’ll stay here outside.

327
00:24:35,634 --> 00:24:36,634
You good?

328
00:24:36,927 --> 00:24:37,761
Yeah.

329
00:24:37,887 --> 00:24:39,722
Did you wash your hands?

330
00:24:40,347 --> 00:24:41,347
Duh!

331
00:24:42,641 --> 00:24:43,851
I had to make sure.

332
00:24:44,810 --> 00:24:46,061
It's common sense.

333
00:24:55,029 --> 00:24:56,030
My hand.

334
00:24:57,198 --> 00:24:59,116
Just take it slow.

335
00:25:08,501 --> 00:25:09,877
Professor Morayta!

336
00:25:10,085 --> 00:25:11,086
Good afternoon!

337
00:25:11,420 --> 00:25:14,089
Good thing you’re awake.
How are you feeling?

338
00:25:15,049 --> 00:25:16,133
Terrible, sir.

339
00:25:16,467 --> 00:25:18,344
I feel like I have a hole in my stomach.

340
00:25:18,928 --> 00:25:22,681
But thanks for bringing me
here to the hospital.

341
00:25:23,933 --> 00:25:25,518
Lorelei mentioned it earlier.

342
00:25:26,268 --> 00:25:27,978
Good thing you got here in time.

343
00:25:28,646 --> 00:25:30,397
Lorelei was so worried about you.

344
00:25:31,815 --> 00:25:34,068
She must’ve prayed to every saint.

345
00:25:34,527 --> 00:25:36,445
Just to make sure you’re safe from danger.

346
00:25:36,862 --> 00:25:37,863
Come on, prof.

347
00:25:38,239 --> 00:25:39,239
Really?

348
00:25:39,657 --> 00:25:42,618
My subconscious said
that you’re also crying.

349
00:25:42,968 --> 00:25:44,637
Why would I cry over you?

350
00:25:46,121 --> 00:25:47,748
We’re not even friends, right?

351
00:25:47,915 --> 00:25:50,125
And maybe something just got in my eye.

352
00:25:50,543 --> 00:25:51,794
Maybe it’s just a cold.

353
00:25:52,169 --> 00:25:53,649
You know, you two look good together.

354
00:25:53,921 --> 00:25:55,005
- What is it, sir?
- What?

355
00:25:55,798 --> 00:25:57,716
I’ve said that to a lot of people,

356
00:25:58,008 --> 00:26:00,427
and they always end up together.

357
00:26:01,136 --> 00:26:02,776
Who knows? Maybe you two are meant to be.

358
00:26:03,180 --> 00:26:05,766
That would make me your matchmaker.

359
00:26:05,975 --> 00:26:07,560
- Nothing like that, sir!
- Impossible!

360
00:26:08,435 --> 00:26:10,271
Okay, if you say so.

361
00:26:10,896 --> 00:26:13,023
Anyway, take care, guys.

362
00:26:13,274 --> 00:26:15,609
Loki. Especially you, Lorelei.

363
00:26:15,818 --> 00:26:18,571
Who ever did this you
has the intention of hurting you.

364
00:26:18,821 --> 00:26:21,365
Remember that, so be careful.

365
00:26:22,700 --> 00:26:24,368
Alright, I have to go.

366
00:26:24,660 --> 00:26:27,079
I still need to visit
my doctor friend here.

367
00:26:27,413 --> 00:26:28,413
Get well soon, Loki.

368
00:26:28,872 --> 00:26:29,872
Thank you, sir.

369
00:26:41,719 --> 00:26:44,138
He seems and sounds
so concerned about us.

370
00:26:45,514 --> 00:26:48,309
We only helped him with a case once.

371
00:26:49,602 --> 00:26:50,602
Wait,

372
00:26:50,811 --> 00:26:52,813
are you suspecting the professor?

373
00:26:54,481 --> 00:26:55,481
A bit.

374
00:26:56,066 --> 00:26:57,192
Why though?

375
00:26:57,526 --> 00:27:00,946
He’s the one
who helped get you to the hospital.

376
00:27:01,322 --> 00:27:02,448
Come on, Loki.

377
00:27:02,489 --> 00:27:03,699
Professor Morayta!

378
00:27:03,824 --> 00:27:06,619
-His name makes me curious.

379
00:27:06,744 --> 00:27:08,287
It gives me an uncanny feeling.

380
00:27:10,122 --> 00:27:11,123
Jim?

381
00:27:11,624 --> 00:27:13,167
What’s so suspicious about that?

382
00:27:13,834 --> 00:27:15,377
Did it remind you of someone?

383
00:27:15,961 --> 00:27:17,630
In some English countries,

384
00:27:18,672 --> 00:27:21,383
Jim is a nickname for James.

385
00:27:22,468 --> 00:27:25,220
So what if Sir’s real name is James?

386
00:27:27,097 --> 00:27:29,183
Haven’t I told you, Lorelei?

387
00:27:31,435 --> 00:27:34,897
Professor Moriarty’s first name is James.

388
00:27:36,899 --> 00:27:38,067
Think about it.

389
00:27:38,776 --> 00:27:42,946
“Morayta” is the Filipino version
of “Moriarty.”

390
00:27:44,365 --> 00:27:47,451
James Moriarty, Jim Morayta.

391
00:27:48,327 --> 00:27:50,454
Doesn’t that seem
a little bit suspicious to you?

392
00:27:56,627 --> 00:27:57,711
Is there a problem?

393
00:27:58,504 --> 00:27:59,963
Nothing, sir.

394
00:28:00,381 --> 00:28:04,009
There are just some small discussions
going on in the Memorial Hall.

395
00:28:05,260 --> 00:28:09,598
But some people are demanding
accountability from the school.

396
00:28:09,723 --> 00:28:12,993
Make sure there’s security
stationed around the area.

397
00:28:13,018 --> 00:28:15,687
I cannot afford
another chaotic incident in this school.

398
00:28:15,688 --> 00:28:16,664
Yes, sir.

399
00:28:16,689 --> 00:28:20,150
Chief Estrada has already dispatched
some police to the area.

400
00:28:20,321 --> 00:28:21,655
Thank you. You may go.

401
00:28:45,759 --> 00:28:47,386
Everything is under control.

402
00:28:51,557 --> 00:28:54,435
Trolls have already been hired
against the Q.E.D. Club.

403
00:29:05,320 --> 00:29:06,320
Come in!

404
00:29:06,989 --> 00:29:08,282
Oh, good eve...

405
00:29:10,576 --> 00:29:11,702
Are you okay, officer?

406
00:29:13,871 --> 00:29:17,040
Sorry, Chief Estrada isn’t here right now.

407
00:29:17,916 --> 00:29:19,626
He’s investigating another case.

408
00:29:22,045 --> 00:29:25,716
Oh, this is Daniel
Geronimo’s autopsy report.

409
00:29:30,846 --> 00:29:31,846
Sorry.

410
00:29:31,930 --> 00:29:33,515
I just noticed...

411
00:29:34,141 --> 00:29:35,934
you seem pretty young.

412
00:29:36,560 --> 00:29:38,020
It’s like we’re the same age.

413
00:29:39,396 --> 00:29:41,732
Yeah, you look like
you just came out of the academy.

414
00:29:42,024 --> 00:29:42,858
Oh, yeah.

415
00:29:42,859 --> 00:29:45,569
I’m still a rookie officer
with the campus police, so…

416
00:29:47,196 --> 00:29:50,365
Sorry, of course I remember you.

417
00:29:50,949 --> 00:29:54,035
We’ve just been a little preoccupied
solving cases,

418
00:29:54,036 --> 00:29:56,288
so we haven’t really gotten
to talk to you much.

419
00:29:56,622 --> 00:29:57,706
It’s okay, it’s okay.

420
00:29:57,915 --> 00:29:58,999
A rookie, huh?

421
00:30:00,292 --> 00:30:02,544
Is that why they’re asking you
to run errands?

422
00:30:03,629 --> 00:30:06,757
How many crime scenes
have you worked, Officer…

423
00:30:09,218 --> 00:30:10,636
Just call me Bastien. Just Bastien.

424
00:30:11,053 --> 00:30:13,806
During my first month
at the campus police station,

425
00:30:14,473 --> 00:30:16,892
I was mostly on desk duty.

426
00:30:16,975 --> 00:30:19,185
But this year, they started taking me
to crime scenes,

427
00:30:19,186 --> 00:30:21,438
so I’m still a little nervous.

428
00:30:22,105 --> 00:30:23,524
So, that’s the…

429
00:30:25,108 --> 00:30:26,108
Take a look.

430
00:30:26,985 --> 00:30:30,571
Traces of Atropa belladonna and hemlock
were found in the victim's system.

431
00:30:30,572 --> 00:30:33,908
The ingestion of their poisons
resulted in anticholinergics syndrome

432
00:30:33,909 --> 00:30:35,429
and respiratory failure, respectively.

433
00:30:35,494 --> 00:30:36,494
Hemlock?

434
00:30:36,620 --> 00:30:40,123
Poison hemlock is one of the plants
that contains toxic alkaloids.

435
00:30:40,624 --> 00:30:42,124
Depending on the dosage,

436
00:30:42,125 --> 00:30:45,504
symptoms can appear
anywhere from 30 minutes to three hours.

437
00:30:45,879 --> 00:30:51,635
As the chief medical examiner said,
toxins act fast once ingested.

438
00:30:52,135 --> 00:30:53,220
So…

439
00:30:53,720 --> 00:30:56,430
if the victim had been taken
to the hospital right away,

440
00:30:56,431 --> 00:30:58,183
he might’ve still survived.

441
00:30:59,226 --> 00:31:03,856
You’re lucky you didn’t get
the tea bag with hemlock.

442
00:31:04,273 --> 00:31:05,357
It’s not luck,

443
00:31:07,359 --> 00:31:08,359
it’s instinct.

444
00:31:08,986 --> 00:31:11,405
Do you mind
if I sniff the scent of these teas?

445
00:31:12,739 --> 00:31:13,740
Be my guest.

446
00:31:15,409 --> 00:31:18,202
Both teas had the same color and scent,

447
00:31:18,203 --> 00:31:21,456
so I thought of another factor
to consider before choosing.

448
00:31:24,710 --> 00:31:26,961
And I noticed
that there’s a slight difference

449
00:31:26,962 --> 00:31:28,547
between the two tea bags.

450
00:31:29,256 --> 00:31:31,717
I made my choice
based on their appearance.

451
00:31:34,595 --> 00:31:36,471
But no matter what you say,

452
00:31:36,805 --> 00:31:37,973
it was still luck.

453
00:31:38,348 --> 00:31:42,895
You gambled on a 50/50 chance
of getting the tea without hemlock.

454
00:31:43,520 --> 00:31:46,231
You don’t even know
what a dried hemlock plant looks like.

455
00:31:47,441 --> 00:31:48,483
Whatever you say.

456
00:31:48,942 --> 00:31:50,944
If you don’t have any more questions,

457
00:31:51,194 --> 00:31:52,820
I’ll head to the police station first.

458
00:31:52,821 --> 00:31:54,531
I only extended my shift a bit.

459
00:31:54,907 --> 00:31:57,658
And, Loki, get well, okay?

460
00:31:57,659 --> 00:31:59,286
Lori, I’ll go ahead.

461
00:31:59,369 --> 00:32:00,954
- Alright, officer.
- Bye, thank you!

462
00:32:06,084 --> 00:32:07,502
- Sorry.
- Sorry.

463
00:32:09,546 --> 00:32:11,423
Loki, Lori. Thank you.

464
00:32:18,180 --> 00:32:19,180
What?

465
00:32:19,932 --> 00:32:21,391
Just checking if I’m still alive?

466
00:32:22,100 --> 00:32:24,144
Or are you here to finish the job?

467
00:32:24,478 --> 00:32:28,065
Did you seriously think
that I wish for my brother’s death?

468
00:32:29,524 --> 00:32:30,609
By the way, Lorelei...

469
00:32:31,485 --> 00:32:34,570
on behalf of the Mendez family,
thank you for taking care of him.

470
00:32:34,571 --> 00:32:35,571
It’s nothing.

471
00:32:35,948 --> 00:32:36,948
Anytime.

472
00:32:37,491 --> 00:32:38,617
It’s my pleasure.

473
00:32:39,743 --> 00:32:43,538
Did you come here to take photos of me
while I’m at my most vulnerable state?

474
00:32:44,289 --> 00:32:47,541
Now you’re thinking of using them
to blackmail me someday,

475
00:32:47,542 --> 00:32:49,461
so I can be a dog to do your bidding?

476
00:32:51,046 --> 00:32:52,047
Sorry, but...

477
00:32:53,423 --> 00:32:54,675
that won’t work on me.

478
00:32:55,842 --> 00:32:58,553
Loki, see,
I didn’t come here to fight you.

479
00:32:59,262 --> 00:33:02,140
Prof Morayta told me what happened to you.

480
00:33:02,683 --> 00:33:06,019
And as your older brother,
I’m just here to check on you.

481
00:33:07,771 --> 00:33:09,439
Your obligation as a brother.

482
00:33:10,065 --> 00:33:13,402
So what, do I still owe you?
Am I supposed to be touched?

483
00:33:15,529 --> 00:33:18,865
You know, it’s ironic
because I did warn you.

484
00:33:19,658 --> 00:33:21,493
Stop looking for M.

485
00:33:22,703 --> 00:33:24,997
You’ve faced M’s minions twice,

486
00:33:25,205 --> 00:33:28,125
and you've seen what they’re capable of.

487
00:33:30,002 --> 00:33:31,461
You never learn, huh?

488
00:33:32,045 --> 00:33:33,045
Well,

489
00:33:33,338 --> 00:33:34,881
the more minions we encounter,

490
00:33:35,632 --> 00:33:37,592
the more pieces of information we get.

491
00:33:38,093 --> 00:33:39,136
So don’t rush,

492
00:33:40,220 --> 00:33:41,680
we’ll catch him eventually.

493
00:33:42,347 --> 00:33:44,099
What, Lorelei? Are you…

494
00:33:44,683 --> 00:33:46,560
Are you just gonna go on
with his bullshit?

495
00:33:47,477 --> 00:33:49,187
You knew it was gonna be dangerous.

496
00:33:49,646 --> 00:33:51,523
And you’re still going to continue this?

497
00:33:53,233 --> 00:33:55,318
Do you really want her
to be the next Rhea?

498
00:34:02,576 --> 00:34:04,995
If the club wants to handle a case,

499
00:34:05,829 --> 00:34:06,997
I’ll make it happen,

500
00:34:07,205 --> 00:34:09,708
because it’s my duty
as a member of the club.

501
00:34:10,417 --> 00:34:11,460
But if not,

502
00:34:11,918 --> 00:34:15,255
I’ll just let it be and stay out of it.

503
00:34:16,381 --> 00:34:17,924
That’s my position!

504
00:34:20,594 --> 00:34:21,636
Let’s get this straight.

505
00:34:22,679 --> 00:34:24,931
Rhea’s name does not mean death,

506
00:34:25,432 --> 00:34:26,683
and it never will.

507
00:34:27,851 --> 00:34:29,770
Have some respect, will you?

508
00:34:32,147 --> 00:34:33,356
My apologies then.

509
00:34:35,400 --> 00:34:36,526
But are you sure?

510
00:34:37,069 --> 00:34:39,571
I can’t stop you from this craziness?

511
00:34:41,114 --> 00:34:42,114
Not anymore.

512
00:34:43,158 --> 00:34:44,158
Get out of here.

513
00:34:49,664 --> 00:34:53,752
You know, I just hope I don’t end up
seeing either of you in the morgue.

514
00:34:54,669 --> 00:34:58,131
And if I do,
you will no longer hear me saying...

515
00:34:59,424 --> 00:35:00,717
I told you so.

516
00:35:24,783 --> 00:35:28,953
Do you remember
what John Bautista said about M

517
00:35:28,954 --> 00:35:32,457
when he was interviewed
by the campus police?

518
00:35:32,666 --> 00:35:33,875
Which one?

519
00:35:34,042 --> 00:35:38,130
He said he talks to M over the phone.

520
00:35:39,881 --> 00:35:43,176
Can you describe his voice?

521
00:35:43,593 --> 00:35:44,845
Just...

522
00:35:45,512 --> 00:35:48,098
cold and deep.

523
00:35:51,268 --> 00:35:52,643
The kind that...

524
00:35:52,644 --> 00:35:56,523
The kind that sends chills
down your spine when you hear it.

525
00:35:59,401 --> 00:36:02,571
Luthor’s voice matches that description.

526
00:36:03,363 --> 00:36:06,032
Deep, cold,

527
00:36:06,408 --> 00:36:08,076
and chilling.

528
00:36:09,244 --> 00:36:10,829
I noticed that too.

529
00:36:12,372 --> 00:36:15,750
Did it ever cross your mind

530
00:36:16,543 --> 00:36:19,087
that your brother is Moriarty?

531
00:36:19,963 --> 00:36:21,756
What makes you think that way?

532
00:36:22,215 --> 00:36:26,845
Loki, Luthor is the Vice President
of the Student Council.

533
00:36:27,637 --> 00:36:31,266
Just like you said before,
he’s the one in control of this.

534
00:36:31,516 --> 00:36:35,187
I assume he also has a lot
of influence on campus.

535
00:36:35,562 --> 00:36:40,609
He’s in the perfect position
to do terrible things.

536
00:36:42,611 --> 00:36:44,738
My brother may be despicable,

537
00:36:45,989 --> 00:36:47,699
but he’s not a monster.

538
00:36:48,783 --> 00:36:51,828
He gets what he wants
through manipulation

539
00:36:52,162 --> 00:36:53,496
but not murder.

540
00:36:54,080 --> 00:36:57,083
Yeah, his voice is chilling,

541
00:36:57,459 --> 00:36:59,169
but it doesn’t mean anything.

542
00:36:59,586 --> 00:37:02,297
- But there’s a possibility...
- I get where you’re coming from.

543
00:37:03,131 --> 00:37:05,425
But he's not M.

544
00:37:17,812 --> 00:37:20,982
Serena did not deserve to die this way.

545
00:37:21,733 --> 00:37:25,487
She’s my friend.
She still had so many dreams.

546
00:37:26,529 --> 00:37:28,155
What I can’t accept

547
00:37:28,156 --> 00:37:31,952
is that she was a strong,
confident, independent woman,

548
00:37:32,494 --> 00:37:34,537
and her life just ended like that.

549
00:37:35,872 --> 00:37:37,623
According to the Q.E.D. Club,

550
00:37:37,624 --> 00:37:40,919
someone’s orchestrating the murders
at this school.

551
00:37:42,128 --> 00:37:44,171
Someone needs
to be held accountable for this!

552
00:37:44,172 --> 00:37:45,673
Justice for Serena!

553
00:37:45,674 --> 00:37:47,132
Justice for Isaac!

554
00:37:47,133 --> 00:37:48,884
President Alcantara is useless!

555
00:37:49,178 --> 00:37:50,555
Defend for Clark U!

556
00:37:50,595 --> 00:37:53,598
Right! You guys are wrong! They are wrong!

557
00:37:54,349 --> 00:37:55,558
You guys are wrong!

558
00:37:56,142 --> 00:37:57,352
You guys are wrong!

559
00:37:58,937 --> 00:38:02,315
Campus Police, it’s chaos here.
Please do something.

560
00:38:02,440 --> 00:38:03,650
Stop it already. Come on.

561
00:38:05,610 --> 00:38:06,736
Liar!

562
00:38:14,160 --> 00:38:16,204
Do you really want her to be the next Rhea?

563
00:38:16,955 --> 00:38:20,417
I just hope I don’t end up seeing
either of you in the morgue.

564
00:38:20,500 --> 00:38:24,004
And if I do,
you will no longer hear me saying...

565
00:38:25,171 --> 00:38:26,715
I told you so.

566
00:38:29,301 --> 00:38:30,593
That’s pretty deep.

567
00:38:32,929 --> 00:38:34,764
- Nurse Melissa.
- Hi.

568
00:38:34,931 --> 00:38:37,016
So you're a resident here?

569
00:38:37,017 --> 00:38:39,227
Yes. How’s Loki doing?

570
00:38:39,728 --> 00:38:41,521
So you heard about it.

571
00:38:42,105 --> 00:38:44,774
He’s doing okay. He’s recovering now.

572
00:38:45,483 --> 00:38:49,571
I understand why your sigh was so deep.

573
00:38:49,696 --> 00:38:53,491
Just earlier,
I heard the students were in an uproar.

574
00:38:53,700 --> 00:38:56,786
Because they all have different opinions
about what’s happening.

575
00:38:57,245 --> 00:38:59,497
Some of them want justice.

576
00:38:59,664 --> 00:39:01,499
Others are still in denial.

577
00:39:02,584 --> 00:39:03,710
My God.

578
00:39:04,502 --> 00:39:09,591
Sometimes, I think
bad luck is really following me.

579
00:39:10,383 --> 00:39:14,346
From my previous school
all the way here at Clark U,

580
00:39:14,721 --> 00:39:15,972
I carried it with me.

581
00:39:17,057 --> 00:39:22,979
What if I just let Loki
deal with the cases by himself?

582
00:39:23,730 --> 00:39:26,775
Maybe then he won’t be put
in danger anymore.

583
00:39:27,525 --> 00:39:28,902
The thing is...

584
00:39:29,986 --> 00:39:31,488
if I stay away from him,

585
00:39:32,364 --> 00:39:35,367
how sure am I this will all stop?

586
00:39:38,828 --> 00:39:42,331
It’s okay to think about those things.

587
00:39:42,332 --> 00:39:46,960
But whatever you decide,
make sure it comes from good intentions.

588
00:39:46,961 --> 00:39:49,004
And stop blaming yourself.

589
00:39:49,005 --> 00:39:51,424
None of what’s happening is your fault.

590
00:39:51,668 --> 00:39:55,797
What happened to Loki isn’t your fault.
It’s not you.

591
00:39:57,283 --> 00:39:58,659
Thank you, Nurse Mel.

592
00:40:00,657 --> 00:40:03,660
I really just want all of this to be over.

593
00:40:04,403 --> 00:40:07,657
I just don’t know how or when.

594
00:40:09,296 --> 00:40:11,131
Only time will tell.

595
00:40:11,432 --> 00:40:13,893
Not everything has to be rushed.

596
00:40:14,489 --> 00:40:19,577
But sometimes, maybe you need
to go through it to learn something.

597
00:40:20,078 --> 00:40:24,457
Be open to make mistakes,
just learn from it.

598
00:40:53,862 --> 00:40:54,696
Hello?

599
00:40:54,697 --> 00:40:55,780
Hello, Lori!

600
00:40:56,072 --> 00:40:57,198
Lori’s not here.

601
00:40:57,907 --> 00:40:59,284
Can you please stop calling?

602
00:41:01,844 --> 00:41:03,012
Loki?

603
00:41:03,318 --> 00:41:04,486
Where’s Lori?

604
00:41:04,622 --> 00:41:05,665
I don’t know.

605
00:41:06,736 --> 00:41:07,737
She went outside.

606
00:41:08,997 --> 00:41:10,290
If it’s not urgent,

607
00:41:11,187 --> 00:41:12,355
call her later.

608
00:41:12,460 --> 00:41:14,587
I really need to talk to her.

609
00:41:14,747 --> 00:41:16,749
Things are getting
a little chaotic at the...

610
00:41:17,729 --> 00:41:18,939
Wait.

611
00:41:19,605 --> 00:41:21,065
You’re in the hospital, right?

612
00:41:21,890 --> 00:41:23,641
Yeah. So what?

613
00:41:23,975 --> 00:41:26,394
So if you’re in the hospital,

614
00:41:26,811 --> 00:41:29,397
that means Lori’s alone
at the Q.E.D. Club right now?

615
00:41:30,070 --> 00:41:32,072
Can she solve cases on her own?

616
00:41:32,108 --> 00:41:33,942
You know, I can help her

617
00:41:33,943 --> 00:41:37,071
so she won’t have to do it alone
or struggle too much.

618
00:41:37,572 --> 00:41:39,407
Just let me join your club already.

619
00:41:40,200 --> 00:41:41,534
That’s still a no.

620
00:41:41,576 --> 00:41:43,161
But why though...

621
00:41:46,664 --> 00:41:49,292
He's so grumpy. He could at least...

622
00:41:53,254 --> 00:41:54,254
Loki?

623
00:41:56,966 --> 00:41:59,886
Oh, my God! Oh, my God, Loki!

624
00:42:01,596 --> 00:42:05,391
What kind of mess
did you get yourself into, huh?

625
00:42:05,433 --> 00:42:07,810
This kid... Wait.

626
00:42:09,687 --> 00:42:12,273
- Where’s Lori?
- Hey, Tita Martha.

627
00:42:13,107 --> 00:42:14,442
- You're here?
- Wait.

628
00:42:14,484 --> 00:42:18,487
- How are you? Do you feel anything?
- No, I'm okay.

629
00:42:18,488 --> 00:42:19,906
- Are you sure? Huh?
- I'm fine.

630
00:42:19,948 --> 00:42:21,282
Are you okay? Huh?

631
00:42:21,574 --> 00:42:23,283
- You’re not feeling anything?
- I'm okay.

632
00:42:23,284 --> 00:42:25,912
If you’re okay, then why...
Where did you come from?

633
00:42:27,121 --> 00:42:29,206
Sorry, Tita.
I just went out to get some air.

634
00:42:29,207 --> 00:42:30,792
- Got some air?
- Yeah.

635
00:42:31,334 --> 00:42:33,628
You’re not supposed to leave him alone!

636
00:42:33,670 --> 00:42:36,214
What is it with you two? My God!

637
00:42:37,549 --> 00:42:42,470
Lori, Loki, do you know
I almost had a heart attack, huh?

638
00:42:42,845 --> 00:42:44,681
When I got your text.

639
00:42:45,515 --> 00:42:48,934
You two are unbelievable.
What's wrong with you two?

640
00:42:48,935 --> 00:42:53,606
You shouldn’t be drinking
whatever people offer you.

641
00:42:53,982 --> 00:42:56,400
Just to be safe,
why don’t you bring your own tumbler?

642
00:42:56,401 --> 00:42:59,654
Aren’t those trendy
with young people these days?

643
00:42:59,779 --> 00:43:01,698
Why don’t you just drink
from those instead?

644
00:43:03,783 --> 00:43:05,118
- Tita?
- What?

645
00:43:05,493 --> 00:43:07,161
- Would you like something to drink?
- Yes!

646
00:43:07,912 --> 00:43:09,580
I can buy you something from the canteen.

647
00:43:09,581 --> 00:43:11,165
Alright! Anywhere’s fine! Your call!

648
00:43:12,779 --> 00:43:13,987
Can you buy me coffee?

649
00:43:14,012 --> 00:43:15,852
- You can't have coffee!
- You can't have coffee!

650
00:43:17,391 --> 00:43:19,977
- Alright, I’ll head out first.
- Hurry up! Go on!

651
00:43:24,683 --> 00:43:26,018
Do you want some fruit?

652
00:43:29,271 --> 00:43:33,234
- Yes, ma'am? Okay.
- Hello, miss! One soda, please.

653
00:43:35,565 --> 00:43:37,483
- Ma'am.
- Thank you.

654
00:43:38,943 --> 00:43:42,071
Paging Dr. De Vera, to the ER, please.

655
00:43:42,363 --> 00:43:44,741
Dr. De Vera, to the ER.

656
00:43:45,283 --> 00:43:48,411
Paging Dr. Sy, to the OR, please.

657
00:43:48,911 --> 00:43:50,872
Dr. Sy, to the OR.

658
00:44:02,592 --> 00:44:06,303
Paging Dr. Sanchez,
please proceed to the Nurse Station.

659
00:44:06,304 --> 00:44:09,307
-Dr. Sanchez, to the Nurse Station, please.

660
00:44:10,016 --> 00:44:15,063
Paging Dr. Uy, please proceed to the ER.
Dr. Uy, to the ER, please.

661
00:45:08,522 --> 00:45:10,024
Do I know you, miss?

662
00:45:11,615 --> 00:45:13,116
Did I do something wrong to you?

663
00:45:13,493 --> 00:45:14,869
Sorry, sir.

664
00:45:15,540 --> 00:45:17,750
Sorry, I bothered you.

665
00:45:18,501 --> 00:45:19,752
I startled you.

666
00:45:20,743 --> 00:45:21,743
Okay.

667
00:45:23,798 --> 00:45:27,218
Sir, what song are you whistling?

668
00:45:27,719 --> 00:45:29,220
Isn’t that a children’s song?

669
00:45:30,012 --> 00:45:31,097
Yeah.

670
00:45:31,576 --> 00:45:32,785
What was that again?

671
00:45:33,319 --> 00:45:34,611
Mary Had a Little Lamb?

672
00:45:34,636 --> 00:45:36,054
That’s it! Right!

673
00:45:38,037 --> 00:45:39,372
I think it was a keypad tone.

674
00:45:39,802 --> 00:45:41,178
I heard someone dialing.

675
00:45:42,608 --> 00:45:44,026
Where did you hear that?

676
00:45:44,915 --> 00:45:46,415
There, inside the CR.

677
00:45:46,440 --> 00:45:47,775
Thank you, sir.

678
00:46:05,047 --> 00:46:06,382
Who are you?

679
00:46:07,383 --> 00:46:08,800
Lorelei!

680
00:46:08,825 --> 00:46:11,328
Moriarty.

681
00:46:11,429 --> 00:46:13,305
Moria...

682
00:46:13,472 --> 00:46:15,182
Moriarty.

683
00:46:16,017 --> 00:46:17,851
Moria...

684
00:46:17,852 --> 00:46:21,397
- Moria...
- Moriarty.

685
00:46:26,486 --> 00:46:27,612
Over here.

686
00:46:36,078 --> 00:46:38,626
It’s not safe
to be out this late by yourself.

687
00:46:55,181 --> 00:46:56,181
Hey.

688
00:46:56,753 --> 00:47:00,298
Our normal counting system
is called “base ten.”

689
00:47:00,478 --> 00:47:03,073
I’m here to formally let you know

690
00:47:03,098 --> 00:47:06,643
that our EIC wants to include
some of your works.

691
00:47:07,049 --> 00:47:09,861
- What?
- I wanted to bring a case to you.

692
00:47:09,862 --> 00:47:12,299
Of course! What is it?

693
00:47:15,995 --> 00:47:17,246
He's such a loser.

694
00:47:20,471 --> 00:47:23,057
I want you to write it in a secured drive.

695
00:47:23,125 --> 00:47:24,961
Do you have a case
you want to bring to us?

696
00:47:25,461 --> 00:47:29,799
I do, actually.
Someone’s been bothering my friend.

697
00:47:30,469 --> 00:47:31,994
But it’s okay! It’s okay!

698
00:47:32,019 --> 00:47:34,480
Maybe next time,
when your partner gets back.

